    "ideation": "The level slider is a performance of calibration and precision. Instead of a human emotion, the robot becomes a high-fidelity audio interface. The eyes act as dual VU meters, moving vertically (gaze_y) while their scale indicates signal strength. The mouth is the raw waveform, shifting from a low-gain hum to a high-amplitude peak that eventually 'clips' into a flat-line gritted frequency. The arc follows a sound engineer's touch: finding the signal, pushing it to the limit, hitting the red, and then settling back into a perfect, balanced unity gain. Colors shift from safe signal green to warning yellow and finally clipping red.",
